			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bard holding aggro?  Charm/Snare?<a name="23571"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 2:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been lurking these boards for some time now, collecting information and such, but one thing I haven't really found is a <u>definitive</u> post on how bards can best hold aggro.  Alot of times I find myself in a caster heavy group and I would really be the best man to tank.  Unfortunately, I find my ability to keep mobs off casters is weak at best, and usually bouncy aggro happens after the mob is at 80%, which is just a pain for everyone involved.
<br />

<br />
So far, it seems the overriding opinion on how to keep aggro is just twist 4 DoT's with TDoK equipped.  However, it never seems to work particularly well for me, and once the mob has switched it's attention to a caster, it will almost never be enough to taunt a mob back to me unless the caster runs far out of range.  The other additional downside is obviously if you are twisting 4 DoT's then no Muse/Manasong, which would be hugely beneficial for said caster gorup.
<br />

<br />
I read once that twisting in lvl 27 manafree charm song every rotation is great for keeping aggro, even though it will resist every time.  Has anyone confirmed this?  Is the taunt factor for charm inherently higher, or is it no better than twisting any other debuff since charm is never landing?
<br />

<br />
What about snare?  Rangers seem to live by snare taunt when tanking.  Does Largo's have the same taunt factor?  Is it higher than a DoT?  
<br />

<br />
Seems like an adequate caster/taunt twist might be something along the lines of Manasong/Charm/Muse/Snare... anyone tried anything like this?  I have been playing around with it for the past few weeks, but really have no definitive data.
<br />

<br />
One other comment, it seems like with the new Weapon Affinity AA, a good way to keep aggro would be to throw a Guk stun proc on a Copper Hammer (or some other stun weapon) with full WA.  Anyone tried anything like this?  Does it hold aggro well, or is it still spotty?  If it does work well, this will probably be the first AA I get in GoD, as I always love finding ways I can fit into new roles that weren't previously possible.
<br />

<br />
Thanks,
<br />
Realobs
<br />
Solusek Ro
<br />
</span></td>
