			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard holding aggro?  Charm/Snare?<a name="23598"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 3:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
A bard holding aggro is definitely doable.  The only problem is
<br />
that it's a lot of work.  And a 3 song twist is already a lot of
<br />
work to certain people, so you'll rarely see bards hold aggro.
<br />

<br />
The best &quot;snap&quot; aggro for a bard is landing assonance and
<br />
bellow at once.  If you're in a large race illusion you can also
<br />
slam for that little extra hate bonus.
<br />

<br />
You don't &quot;need&quot; to twist 4 dots to keep aggro.  If you stand
<br />
close to the mob and melee, click in drums to do full dot
<br />
damage, you only need 2 dots to keep aggro, 3 to be safe.
<br />

<br />
In a small group of people I know, fire dot, magic dot, muse,
<br />
zek, marr, assonance, silent song, and lullaby are my 8 songs
<br />
up.  In a full group of people I don't know, if I need to tank
<br />
it'll be 3 dots, muse, marr, assonance, silent song, lullaby.
<br />

<br />
As for largo's, much like our other non-damage slows, largo's
<br />
is coded to give very little to no aggro at all.  I tried charm
<br />
and fear songs to gain aggro and it didn't work at all.  I also
<br />
tried shield of songs and didn't notice anything either.
<br />

<br />
When it comes to weapons, bards are coded to not receive
<br />
hate from stuns/debuffs like other classes would.  So another
<br />
melee class using that copper hammer will get a ton of aggro
<br />
meanwhile you can proc it 10 times and the mob will still pound
<br />
the cleric.  Same thing for weapons with snare, slow, or tash
<br />
type effects.  So best economical bet would be to go for a
<br />
lifetap effect, since you get DD and heal aggro at once.
<br />

<br />
If money/time is no object, get a Blade of Carnage (since the
<br />
effect is pure hate, the bard code doesn't mitigate it), or go
<br />
to veksar and get that Hooked Shan'kor (spelling?).  You can't
<br />
rely on the weapon to keep aggro alone, but it will make it
<br />
easier on your dot twist if you own one.
<br />

<br />
If you're going to be taking the hits tho, max defensive aa's a
<br />
are definite super-plus.  Max dex/agi, and dodge/parry/riposte
<br />
mod items are also very recommended.  You can never have
<br />
enough hp/ac, so keep getting more.  High charisma is good
<br />
too.  Be a buff whore!
<br />

<br />
We're never going to mitigate as well as warriors, and we dont
<br />
have the super-easy hate knights get either.  But a bard-tank
<br />
can be an option, if you're willing to work really hard.
<br />

<br />
Of course some critics won't be satisfied until a bard tanks
<br />
Quarm or some super-uber GoD boss mob, and unfortunately
<br />
for me I'm not even elemental flagged yet.  In the zones I xp
<br />
in however, mainly BoT and Tactics, I tank very well.  I've
<br />
tanked all the nameds in the BoT wings except for Laef.  The
<br />
groups I was in were amazed, but I'm sure some people on 
<br />
these boards will just scoff at my accomplishments.
<br />

<br />
good luck!
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
