			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard holding aggro?  Charm/Snare?<a name="23613"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 24 04 4:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I tank every single day with my bard, and I will let you in on a little technique that everyone always marvels at when I pull it out.  Because of this marvel-factor, be SURE to explain the technique to your group before you use it, or they will all be very upset at you.
<br />

<br />
4 words are the answer to holding aggro indefinitely:
<br />

<br />
Kazumi's Note of Preservation.
<br />

<br />
Hold aggro the way you are currently (whether it be dots, or charms, or whatever).  As soon as a caster or someone gains aggro, sing Kazumi's.  IMMEDIATELY CLICK OFF KAZUMI'S FROM YOUR BUFF LIST.  The mob will be incredibly disinterested in the folks who are invulnerable, and immediately snap back to you.  This gives you about 15 seconds of free aggro-gaining time.  Use this time to build up aggro in any manner you choose fit, but I guarantee that you will have aggro when Kazumi's wears on the other people in your group.
<br />

<br />
Since the repop timer on Kazumi's is only 3 minutes, you can do this about once per pull, depending on how fast your pull rate is.  
<br />

<br />
This is also very useful in groups where you are not the tank, as you can save other folks' lives by explaining to the tank beforehand that you will DA (Divine Aura) everyone if someone is about to die -- and that the tank should immediately click of the buff when it appears.  This can also be used to switch to an OT if the MT is very low and about to die (perhaps the MH died?).
<br />

<br />
Have fun with your bard ghetto-taunt. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Mirthe
<br />
61 Bard
<br />
Quellious</span></td>
