				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Use a Pet<a name="23819"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 12:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A bard pet can be a good way to hold aggro, especially in LDON. Most melee mobs can pump out a lot of DPS. When they are fighting on your side they do a great job of holding the aggro. When charm breaks, the pet is mad at you because you charmed him, and his former target is mad at you because you were the cause of the damage the pet dished out.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, this tactic is subject to level limitations. But when it works, it works well. We get three charm songs. Level 27 charms works on level 37 mobs. Level 39 charm works on level 51 mobs. And level 64 charm works on level 57 mobs. 
<br />

<br />
Spiritomolto
<br />
Bard 55</span></td>
